text.section:
The board shall:
Adopt and provide itself with a seal with a band inscribed, "Kentucky Board of Architects" with the coat of arms of the state in the center;
Promulgate all necessary administrative regulations concerning the contents and conduct of examinations, the method and time for filing applications for examinations, and the time within which an applicant shall be examined after his application has been filed;
Keep a complete record of its proceedings and an accurate list of all applications made, licenses issued, and licenses revoked; and
Make a general report including finances to the governor annually.
